Package org.garret.perst

Interface EmbeddedLink<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Collection<T>, ITable<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>, Link<T>, java.util.List<T>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public interface EmbeddedLink<T>
extends Link<T>
    There are two kind of links in Perst: embedded and implemented as standalone object (collection). This interface extends Link interface with getOwner/setOwner methods allowing to bind link with its container. Such binding is needed for embedded link implementation to make modify() in link methods work properly. This interface is needed mostly if you are going to provide you own implementation of embedded links.
